A Nepalese teenager killed herself after Brazil's 7-1 World Cup semi-final defeat to Germany.

Police said 15-year-old Pragya Thapa was depressed after her favourite team's thrashing and hanged herself on Wednesday morning in Bharaul - a village 250 miles east of the capital Kathmandu.

The 10th grade student was found by her mother hanging from her ceiling in her room. Thapa was living with her mother and grandparents 
while her father was abroad working.

